# Babel Plugin (`babel-plugin-jsx-dom-expressions`)

## Overview

Compiles JSX into optimized DOM creation code. Supports three output modes: `dom` (client), `ssr` (server), and `universal` (custom renderers). Built with Rollup.

## Entry Point

`src/index.ts` — exports a Babel plugin that inherits `@babel/plugin-syntax-jsx` and visits `JSXElement`, `JSXFragment`, and `Program` nodes.

## Source Structure

- `src/shared/` — mode-agnostic logic
  - `transform.js` — main JSX transformation entry
  - `preprocess.js` — `Program:enter` setup
  - `postprocess.js` — `Program:exit` cleanup (template insertion)
  - `component.js` — component element handling
  - `fragment.js` — fragment handling
  - `utils.js` — AST utilities and helpers
  - `validate.js` — JSX validation
- `src/dom/` — DOM-mode code generation
  - `element.js` — native element transformation
  - `template.js` — template creation and cloning
  - `constants.js` — DOM-specific constants
- `src/ssr/` — SSR-mode code generation
  - `element.js`, `template.js`
- `src/universal/` — universal-mode code generation
  - `element.js`, `template.js`
- `src/config.ts` — plugin configuration and defaults

HTML facts (void elements, raw-text elements, delegated events, namespaces, MathML/SVG element sets, child-property/state-property mappings) live in `dom-expressions/src/constants` and are imported from there — the babel plugin does not maintain its own copies.

## Key Concepts

- **Templates**: Static HTML is extracted into `template()` calls that create `<template>` elements once and clone them. Dynamic parts are patched via `effect()` wrappers.
- **Component calls**: `<Comp prop={val}>` compiles to `createComponent(Comp, { prop: val })`.
- **Delegated events**: Events in `DelegatedEvents` set are compiled to use event delegation (`$$click`) instead of `addEventListener`.
- **Spreads**: Dynamic props use `spread()` runtime call.

## Build

- `pnpm build` — Rollup build (`rollup -c --bundleConfigAsCjs`)
- `pnpm test` — builds first, then runs Jest
- Output: `index.js` (CJS)
